We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the:
A. Municipal Treasurer
1. to cancel the unclaimed stale checks and furnish the accountant with the original Disbursement Vouchers (DV) and its supporting documents;
2. to secure the addresses of the payees for notification of the return of stale checks in their possession for replacement;
3. to confirm with the depository banks the errors posted in their bank accounts; and
4. to prepare at yearend a List of Unreleased Checks to be attached to the Report of Checks Issued and submit to the Municipal Accountant and to COA Auditor;
B. Municipal Accountant
5. to review the long outstanding/stale checks and 6. to prepare the Journal Entry Voucher for stale checks following the adjusting entries below: a. for stale checks over 6 months but not over 2 yrs.: DR: Cash in Bank-LCCA Pxx CR: Accounts Payable Pxx; b. for checks over 2 yrs.: DR: Cash in Bank- LCCA Pxx CR: Prior Year’s Adjustment* Pxx (*to represent surplus adjustment);
7. to identify and look for the supporting documents relative to the computed variance of P10,000.00 in the Cash in bank accounts under the Special Education and Trust Funds; and
8. to restore unreleased checks by preparing a journal entry voucher at the end of the year based on the list submitted from the MTO. At the start of the ensuing year, draw another entry to reverse the previous entry made and recognize the availability of the checks for release;

